description: Probably a back-formation from tampin (misinterpreted as tamping), a variant of tampion.

verbs.description: tamp (third-person singular simple present tamps, present participle tamping, simple past and past participle tamped)

entries.meaning: (blasting) To plug up with clay, earth, dry sand, sod, or other material, as a hole bored in a rock.
To drive in or pack down by frequent gentle strokes
examples: Tamp earth so as to make a smooth place.

verbs.description: tamp (third-person singular simple present tamps, present participle tamping, simple past and past participle tamped)
